OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1784634473
OL,3,CAndy Burnham's cabinet: Who's in and
OL,4,Cwho's out?
OL,6,FManchester Central MP Lucy Powell held
OL,7,Fseveral positions in Starmer's top
OL,8,Fteam, and continues to be Labour's
OL,9,Fdeputy leader, an appointment prompted
OL,10,Fby Rayner's exit from frontline
OL,11,Fpolitics.
OL,13,FShe was the preferred choice of Labour
OL,14,Fmembers for that position, and won it
OL,15,Fover Starmer ally Bridget Phillipson.
OL,17,FAnneliese Midgley ` Chief Whip
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G16/26
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30317
SC,0017
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1784634473
OL,3,CAndy Burnham's cabinet: Who's in and
OL,4,Cwho's out?
OL,6,FMidgley will be a member of the
OL,7,Fcabinet as she takes up the role of
OL,8,Fchief whip, the government's chief
OL,9,Fenforcer in parliament.
OL,11,FThe role may, however, be somewhat
OL,12,Fdifferent under new Prime Minister
OL,13,FBurnham, who has spoken of his dislike
OL,14,Ffor the whipping system used to ensure
OL,15,FMPs vote with the government.
OL,17,FBridget Phillipson ` Women and
OL,18,FEqualities minister
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G17/26
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30318
SC,0018
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1784634473
OL,3,CAndy Burnham's cabinet: Who's in and
OL,4,Cwho's out?
OL,6,FPhillipson, a close ally of Starmer,
OL,7,Fhas lost her job as education
OL,8,Fsecretary, but remains as the minister
OL,9,Ffor women and equalities, and will
OL,10,Fattend Cabinet.
OL,12,FIn that role in Starmer's government,
OL,13,FPhillipson has overseen widely-debated
OL,14,Freforms to Equality and Human Rights
OL,15,FCommission guidance on trans people.
OL,17,FLisa Nandy ` Culture Secretary
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G18/26
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30319
SC,0019
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1784634473
OL,3,CAndy Burnham's cabinet: Who's in and
OL,4,Cwho's out?
OL,6,FLisa Nandy, who has kept her job as
OL,7,Fculture secretary and is a close ally
OL,8,Fof the prime minister, was seen as
OL,9,Fsomething of an outsider in Starmer's
OL,10,Fcabinet, and her Greater Manchester
OL,11,Fconstituency of Wigan borders
OL,12,FBurnham's in Makerfield.
OL,14,FAfter Labour's defeat in the 2019
OL,15,Fgeneral election, Nandy stood in the
OL,16,Fleadership election to replace Jeremy
OL,17,FCorbyn, but she finished third behind
OL,18,FStarmer.
OL,20,FAlex Norris ` Justice Secretary
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G19/26
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
